  notes:
    - "Wave 673 (sk3391): __int__, __float__, __complex__ dict-presence checks for socket types."
    - "Theme: __int__/__float__/__complex__ dict-presence (int(x), float(x), complex(x))."
    - "All values False — hashlib types are cryptographic hash objects with no numeric conversion support."
    - "socket.socket is a Python class; it does not define __int__, __float__, or __complex__ in its __dict__."
    - "socket.AddressFamily and socket.SocketKind are IntEnum subclasses (EnumType metaclass)."
    - "AddressFamily and SocketKind are IntEnum but do NOT define __int__, __float__, or __complex__ in their own __dict__; these methods are not overridden at the subclass level."
    - "operator.contains(socket.AddressFamily.__dict__, '__int__') is False — not present in AddressFamily's own __dict__."
    - "operator.contains(socket.SocketKind.__dict__, '__int__') is False — same reasoning as AddressFamily."
    - "All values are False for all 3 socket types across all 3 operators."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"
error_model: python_exceptions

